Recipe by @lakecomokitchen 🤍 Save for your next pasta night and, better yet, book yourself a trip to Como and take the class for yourself ✨

Ingredients for 8 (2) people:
500g mascarpone (160g)
5 egg yolks (2)
3 egg whites (2)
100g sugar (1 Tb)
1 vanilla bean (1/2) – I highly recommend using a bean, but extract is an alternative
Shot of moscato (splash)
Approx. 250ml of pre-made coffee (tip: make your coffee early and let it cool)
Pinch of salt
Dry finger biscuits
Cacao powder

Method:
• add a pinch of salt to the egg whites and gently whisk into light, fluffy peaks
• in a separate bowl, add sugar, egg yolks and whisk until it changes to a paler/creamy colour
• soften your mascarpone using a fork and add it to the egg yolk and sugar mixture
• whisk again to make sure there are no hidden lumps
• with a spoon, gently fold whisked egg whites into mixture
• add the coffee and moscato together into a bowl to make the dipping mixture
• dip biscuits into this mixture being careful not to get it too soggy
• arrange biscuits in a layer, top with mascarpone, and repeat
• to finish, dust top with cocoa powder
• pop in fridge for 2 hours or overnight
